The paper deals with distributed optimization problems in a network setting, which is a common topic in the field of multi-agent systems (MAS). Therefore, cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes novel algorithms for solving these problems, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper deals with optimization problems, which can be considered as a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), but since the focus is on distributed optimization, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a likely category. The paper also mentions target localization and formation control problems, which are common topics in Robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper deals with optimization problems that are a generalization of linear programs, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
